Please answer the below core-java Questions:

What is programing language?

A programming language is a computer language. It is a set of commands, syntax to interpret into a code to the computer. Programming language uses to create a software.

What jdk contains or composed of and define each components?
A. JDK is a software development environment used for developing Java applications and applets. It  contains JRE, compiler,Interpreter and JAR etc. JRE- It is an environment that is required for executing java application. Java compiler checks the syntax error,converts source code into byte code with the help of JVM, Interpreter executes the program. JAR is an Archive of Java.

What is IDE?
A.Integrated Development Environment- It is tools which is need to write,debug and test the code,

What are the IDEs available in the market to support java?
A.Eclipse,IntelliJ,NetBeans,JDeveloper etc

Explain the entire java life cycle.
There are 3 main stages of java life cycle...Editing the program, compiling the source code and executing the code.

what is class?
A class is blueprint of object , it is a group of objects which has common properties.

What is object?
 Object is an instance of a class. Suppose Bicycle is a class then MountainBicyle,SportsBicycle can be considered as objects of the class.

What is the entry point of an application?
Main() method  is the entry point. It is the first method that is invoked when Java program runs.

Why main is static?
The main purpose of using the static keyword in Java is to save memory.

Which class is the superclass of all classes?
Object is the Super class all all classes.

What is difference between path and classpath variables?
The path defines where the system can find the executable files. Classpath environment variable uses to specify the location of the classes and packages.

What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
An Interface only allows defining functionality,not implementing it.  Abstract class  allows to create functionality Abstract class can have abstract and non-abstract methods..Interface can have only abstract methods. Abstract class doesn't support multiple inheritance. Interface supports multiple inheritance.

Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?
It creates an object of the proxy class which implements that interface. Abstract class and interface can not be instantiated.

what is Access Specifier?
An access specifier is a defining code element that can determine which elements of a program are allowed to access a specific variable  or other piece of data.

What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
Object Oriented Programming combine data and action together and to reuse the codes as and when required.
OOP features are ..object,class,inheritance,polymorphism,abstruction and encapsulation.

What is Java Package and which package is imported by default?
Packages are a folder in java that wraps a group of classes, sub-packages and different interfaces. The default package is a collection of java classes whose source files do not contain and paca=kage declarations. These packages act as the default package for such classes.

What is API? Name list of API that you have used so far.
An  application programming interface is a way for two or more computer programs to communicate with each other. Gmail, google maps,Netflix,Zoom
Does java support multiple inheritance, explain why or why not?
Java does not support multiple inheritances in classes. To prevent ambiguity.

What is method overloading and when it happens?
Overloading is writing the same method with different parameters.Overloading method can have different return types. Overloading happens at compile time.
