What is the difference between JDK and JVM?
JDK is a software development kit that helps in the development of application in Java which provides Java class libraries with necessary components to run java code
JVM executes Java byte code and provides an environment for execute.
What is the difference between JVM and JRE?
JRE provides the minimum requirements for executing a java application and JVM is a java virtual machine.
What is compile time and run time?
Compile time is the period when the programming code is converted to the machine code and Run time is the period of time when a program is running.
